.TH getyx 3
.SH NAME
\*Lgetyx\*O \- Gets the cursor position
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lint getyx(\*Vwin\*L, \*Vy\*L, \*Vx\*L)
    WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L;
    int \*Vy\*L, \*Vx\*L;\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "getyx macro"
The cursor coordinates of the window are placed in the
two integer variables \*Ly\*O and \*Lx\*O.
This routine is implemented as a macro, so no ampersand (&)
is necessary before the variables.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
No return value is defined for this function.
.EQ
